      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Tariffs are a blunt instrument that primarily function as a tax on consumers, forcing them to pay higher prices for goods while offering only a temporary, often illusory shield to domestic industries. While proponents claim they protect local jobs, the reality is that they distort markets, reduce economic efficiency, and ultimately harm the very workers they aim to help by stifling competition and innovation. True protection comes from investing in education, infrastructure, and fair wages, not from imposing trade barriers that punish the average family.",
