    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "But isn't it kind of a false choice to say we have to choose between high prices and national security? If we can't produce our own essential goods locally, aren't we just making ourselves vulnerable? It feels like you're dismissing the whole idea of industrial policy as being 'wrong' when it's clearly a major tool for many successful economies.",
